title: Royals win! Kansas City defeats Houston 7-2, claiming ALDS
text:
Royals win! Kansas City defeats Houston 7-2, claiming ALDS POSTED: 09:55 PM CDT Oct 14, 2015 KANSAS CITY, Mo. - 
The Kansas City Royals have more baseball left in 2015 season. 
Johnny Cueto pitched eight innings, giving up just two runs in the Royals 7-2 victory Wednesday night in Game 5 of the American League Division Series. Kansas City advanced to play the Toronto Blue Jays in the American League Championship. 
Cueto retired 19-straight batters. His lone mistake came in the second-inning. Her served up a two-run home run to Jose Valbuena. The Royals cut the lead to 2-1 in the fourth-inning. The Royals opened the game with a three-run fifth. The big hit came off the bat of Alex Rios. His double scored two runs. 
Kendrys Morales ended the scoring with a three-run home run in the eighth-inning.
